# Meebo Usage

Meebo adds Zod-based runtime validation and auto-generated Swagger/OpenAPI docs to Express routes. Use it for all endpoint definitions.

## Router Setup

Every feature router must use `TypedRouter` with `tag` and `basePath`:

```typescript
import { TypedRouter } from "meebo";
import express from "express";

const BookRouter = TypedRouter(express.Router(), {
  tag: "Books",
  basePath: "/api/v1/books",
});
```

## Route Definitions

Pass controller methods directly as the handler — no `.catch(next)` wrapper needed. Express 5 automatically catches async errors and forwards them to the error middleware.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — pass controller method directly
BookRouter.get("/:id", {
  operationId: "getBookById",
  summary: "Get a book by ID",
  params: z.object({ id: z.string() }),
  response: BookSchema,
}, BookController.getBookById);

// ❌ BAD — unnecessary .catch(next) wrapper
BookRouter.get("/:id", { ... }, (req, res, next) => {
  BookController.getBookById(req, res).catch(next);
});
```

## Non-Standard Endpoints (SSE, streaming, etc.)

For endpoints that don't use standard JSON request/response (e.g. SSE streams), use `skipValidation: true` instead of providing Zod schemas. Still provide `operationId` and `summary`.

```typescript
SyncRouter.get("/sync", {
  operationId: "beginIdentitySync",
  summary: "Start identity sync via SSE",
  skipValidation: true,
}, SyncController.beginIdentitySync);
```

Never use a plain `express.Router()` — always use `TypedRouter` so every endpoint has an `operationId` and `summary`.

## Required Schema Options

| Field | Required | Purpose |
|-------|----------|---------|
| `operationId` | Always | Unique ID for the OpenAPI operation |
| `summary` | Always | Short description shown in Swagger UI |
| `skipValidation` | When needed | Skip Zod validation for non-standard endpoints (SSE, etc.) |
| `tags` | Optional | Override the router-level `tag` |
| `request` | When needed | Zod schema for `req.body` |
| `response` | When needed | Zod schema for the 200 response |
| `responses` | When needed | Map of status code → Zod schema |
| `params` | When needed | Zod schema for `req.params` |
| `query` | When needed | Zod schema for `req.query` |
| `headers` | When needed | Zod schema for `req.headers` |

## Multiple Response Codes

```typescript
BookRouter.get("/:id", {
  operationId: "getBookById",
  summary: "Get a book by ID",
  params: z.object({ id: z.string() }),
  response: BookSchema,
  responses: {
    404: z.object({ error: z.string() }),
    500: z.object({ error: z.string() }),
  },
}, BookController.getBookById);
```

## Schema Metadata

Use `.openapi()` on Zod schemas to enrich Swagger docs:

```typescript
const BookSchema = z.object({
  title: z.string().openapi({ example: "The Great Gatsby" }),
  price: z.number().openapi({ example: 12.99 }),
}).openapi({ description: "A book listing" });
```
